# Security & Authentication Rules

## 🔐 Security Implementation Guidelines

### **Authentication System**
- **JWT Tokens**: Access token (7 days) + Refresh token (30 days)
- **OAuth Integration**: Google and LinkedIn social login
- **Password Security**: bcryptjs hashing with salt rounds
- **Session Management**: Stateless JWT with refresh token rotation

### **Security Middleware Stack**
```javascript
// Security middleware order in server.js
app.use(helmet());                    // Security headers
app.use(rateLimit());                // Rate limiting
app.use(cors());                     // CORS configuration
app.use(compression());              // Response compression
app.use(mongoSanitize());           // NoSQL injection protection
app.use(xssSanitization());          // XSS protection
app.use(passport.initialize());      // Authentication
```

### **JWT Implementation**
- **Access Token**: Short-lived (7 days) for API requests
- **Refresh Token**: Long-lived (30 days) for token renewal
- **Token Storage**: HTTP-only cookies for web, localStorage for mobile
- **Token Rotation**: New refresh token on each renewal

### **Password Security**
```javascript
// Password hashing with bcryptjs
const bcrypt = require('bcryptjs');
const saltRounds = 12;

// Hash password
